==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɔədibl̩/}}

===Adjective===
'''audible'''

# Being able to be [[heard]].
#* '''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: "Now, look here, Jim Hawkins," he said, in a steady whisper, that was no more than '''audible'''...

====Derived terms====
* [[audibly]]

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|audibl|ing}}

# {{fb}} To change the play at the [[line of scrimmage]] by yelling out a new one.
#: ''The quarterback '''audibled''' after seeing the defensive formation.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{fb}} The act of or an instance of changing the play at the [[line of scrimmage]] by yelling out a new one.
#: ''The '''audible''' changed the play to a run.''

===Antonyms===
* [[inaudible]]

